<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (ECSC, EEC, EURATOM) No 4064/88 of 21 December 1988 laying down provisions for applying Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of staff of the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 4064/88, millega kehtestatakse Euroopa Elu- ja T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste Parandamise Fondi personali teenistustingimuste artikli 46a rakenduss&auml;tted 21. detsember 1988 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 1860/76 of 29 June 1976 laying down the Conditions of Employment of staff of the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions (1), as last amended by Council Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 680/87 (2), and in particular Article 46a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1976. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 1860/76, millega kehtestatakse Euroopa Elu- ja T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste Parandamise Fondi personali teenistustingimused, (1) mida on viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 680/87, (2) eriti selle artiklit 46a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Committee of Experts provided for in paragraph 2 of that Article 46a, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse selle artikli 46a l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud ekspertkomisjoni arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of staff of the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions sets out the conditions for granting an unemployment allowance to former staff members who are unemployed following termination of their service with the Foundation; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Euroopa Elu- ja T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste Parandamise Fondi personali teenistustingimused n&auml;evad ette tingimused t&ouml;&ouml;tustoetuse andmiseks varasematele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kes on t&ouml;&ouml;tud p&auml;rast nende teenistuse l&otilde;ppu fondis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for the Commission to lay down such provisions as it deems necessary for applying paragraph 2 of that Article 46a; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon peab selle artikli 46a l&otilde;ike 2 kohaldamiseks ette n&auml;gema s&auml;tted, mida ta vajalikuks peab; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 91/88 (3) lays down provisions for implementing Article 28a of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities, which is identical to Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of Staff of the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working Conditions, </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rus (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 91/88 (3) kehtestab &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste artikli 28a rakenduseeskirjad, mis on identne Euroopa Elu- ja T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste Parandamise Fondi personali teenistustingimuste artikliga 46a, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 91/88, with the exception of Article 5 thereof, shall apply by analogy to staff of the European Foundation for the Improvement of Living and Working conditions. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 91/88 s&auml;tteid, v&auml;lja arvatud selle artiklit 5, kohaldatakse analoogia p&otilde;hjal Euroopa Elu- ja T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste Parandamise Fondi t&ouml;&ouml;tajate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kahek&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 21 December 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 21. detsember 1988 Komisjoni nimel </eesti>
